          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to validate energy usage data. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function checks whether the provided energy usage data meets certain criteria or thresholds, ensuring data integrity and correctness."
